Template: sx1302-hal/enable-spi
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Enable SPI interface on the Raspberry Pi?
 The SX1302 concentrator communicates over SPI. This will add
 dtparam=spi=on to /boot/firmware/config.txt if not already present.
 .
 A reboot is required for changes to take effect.

Template: sx1302-hal/enable-i2c
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Enable I2C interface for temperature measurements?
 The SX1302 concentrator board includes an I2C temperature sensor
 (STTS751) used for thermal compensation. This will add
 dtparam=i2c_arm=on to /boot/firmware/config.txt if not already present.
 .
 A reboot is required for changes to take effect.

Template: sx1302-hal/enable-gps
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Enable GPS serial port for the concentrator?
 If your concentrator board has a GPS module, this will configure
 the serial port by adding enable_uart=1 and disabling the serial
 console in /boot/firmware/config.txt.
 .
 A reboot is required for changes to take effect.

Template: sx1302-hal/gps-device
Type: string
Default: /dev/ttyAMA0
Description: GPS serial device path:
 Specify the serial device connected to the GPS module.

Template: sx1302-hal/reboot-required
Type: note
Description: Reboot required
 SPI, I2C, and/or GPS configuration has been changed in /boot/firmware/config.txt.
 Please reboot the Raspberry Pi for changes to take effect.
